1.  WHY IS SCALA A FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE?

scala is not a fully functional programming language but a hybrid functional programming language. Scala smoothly integrates the features of object-oriented and functional languages. Scala is compiled to run on the Java Virtual Machine.
Scala is a pure object-oriented language in the sense that every value is an object. 
Scala is also a functional language in the sense that every function is a value and every value is an object so ultimately every function is an object.

Scala provides a lightweight syntax for defining anonymous functions, it supports higher-order functions, it allows functions to be nested, and supports currying.
Scala is compiled into Java Byte Code which is executed by the Java Virtual Machine 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2.  DIFFERENCE BETWEEN VAL AND VAR?

VAR :- It is a variable that can change value and this is called mutable variable
VAL :- It is a variable that cannot be changed and this is called immutable variable.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3.  What is an "Object" in Scala?

 A class is a blueprint for objects. Once we define a class, we can create objects from the class blueprint with the keyword new. Through the object we can use all functionalities of the defined class.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4.  What is an Application in Scala and how to define one?

The App trait is a convenient way of creating an executable scala program. The difference to the main method altenative is that the App trait uses the delayed initalization feature.

Objects inheriting the App trait instead make use of Scala 2.9â€™s delayed initialization feature to execute the whole body as part of an inherited main method.

Another new feature of the App scheme is that command line arguments are now accessible via the args value (which is inherited from trait App)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

What is the Unit return type?

It corresponds to no value which is same as void.

